    {
      "name": "Authentic Tomato Scrambled Eggs (番茄炒蛋)",
      "instructions": [
        "Whisk the large free range eggs in a bowl with a pinch of salt and a splash of Shaoxing rice wine.",
        "Halve the cherry tomatoes. Finely chop the scallions, separating the white and green parts, and mince the garlic.",
        "Heat vegetable oil in a wok over medium-high heat. Pour in the eggs and scramble gently until just set but still slightly runny. Remove from the wok and set aside.",
        "Add a little more oil to the wok. Stir-fry the garlic and scallion whites until fragrant.",
        "Add the cherry tomatoes to the wok and cook until they soften and release their juices, pressing lightly with your spatula to create a saucy consistency.",
        "Season with sugar and salt to taste.",
        "Return the scrambled eggs to the wok, gently fold them into the tomato mixture, and drizzle with sesame oil.",
        "Garnish with the scallion greens and serve hot as a classic homestyle dish."
