      "name": "Tomato Egg Drop Soup (番茄蛋花汤)",
      "instructions": [
        "Halve the cherry tomatoes. Thinly slice the ginger and finely chop the scallions.",
        "Mix the cornstarch with two tablespoons of water in a small bowl to make a slurry.",
        "Whisk the large free range eggs in a separate bowl.",
        "Heat a teaspoon of vegetable oil in a pot. Sauté the ginger and cherry tomatoes until the tomatoes soften and begin to break down.",
        "Pour in 750ml of water and bring to a boil. Lower the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.",
        "Stir in the cornstarch slurry to lightly thicken the soup base.",
        "Turn off the heat (or lower to very low) and slowly drizzle in the beaten eggs in a thin stream while stirring gently in one direction to create beautiful, thin egg ribbons.",
        "Season with salt, white pepper powder, and sesame oil. Garnish with chopped scallions and serve immediately."
