    {
      "name": "Tomato and Egg Gravy Noodles (番茄鸡蛋面)",
      "instructions": [
        "Cook the wheat noodles in boiling water according to package instructions, drain, and distribute into serving bowls.",
        "Whisk the large free range eggs with a pinch of salt. Halve the cherry tomatoes, mince the garlic, and chop the scallions.",
        "Heat vegetable oil in a wok and scramble the eggs until softly set. Remove from the wok and set aside.",
        "Add another tablespoon of oil to the wok and fry the garlic and scallion whites until fragrant.",
        "Add the cherry tomatoes and cook until soft and saucy, using a spatula to mash them slightly.",
        "Season the tomatoes with light soy sauce, sugar, and salt. Add a splash of water to make a rich gravy and simmer for 2 minutes.",
        "Stir in the scrambled eggs and simmer for another minute to let the eggs absorb the rich tomato juices.",
        "Ladle the hot tomato and egg gravy over the prepared noodles, garnish with scallion greens, and serve hot."
      ],
      "required_ingredients": [
